org.safs

Interface HookConfig

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DCJavaHook, DefaultHookConfig, DJavaHook, EmbeddedDCHookDriver, EmbeddedHookDriver, EmbeddedSeleniumHookDriver, IJavaHook, JavaHook, JavaSocketsHook, SeleniumHook, SeleniumHookConfig, SeleniumJavaHook

    public interface HookConfig
    In SAFS, the engine and hook will normally run in different JVM. At hook side, we cannot see any settings done at engine side, and we need to get the settings from the ConfigureInterface again so that the hook will know about them.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void checkConfiguration()
      Check the ConfigureInterface to get the settings required by Hook.
